<subSubSection pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,1393,2032]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1572,1599]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A small species that resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[672,819,1573,1599]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Afroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequabilis">
<emphasis box="[672,819,1573,1599]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">A. aequabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a similar body size and appearance, but it can be separated by the elongate forewings that taper apically and end in an acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1171,1608,1635]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–86" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1747,1772]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,200,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[227,1361,200,1699]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 79–86. Afroptera spp. Forewings of the males. 79, A. acuta sp. nov.; 80, A. alba sp. nov.; 81, A. koranna sp. nov.; 82, A. balli sp. nov.; 83, A. cylindrata sp. nov.; 84, A. brinkmani sp. nov.; 85, A. maraisi sp. nov.; 86, A. folia sp. nov. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335146/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[1289,1437,1609,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Afroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequabilis">
<emphasis box="[1289,1437,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">A. aequabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the forewings are broad and end in a narrow rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[829,927,1645,1671]" captionStart="FIGURES 115–122" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1518,1543]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,219,1470]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[227,1361,219,1470]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 115–122. Afroptera spp. Male forewings. 115, A. longicornis (Tjeder); 116, A. munroi (Tjeder); 117, A. aequabilis (Tjeder); 118, A. sabuleti (Tjeder); 119, A. olivacea (Tjeder); 120, A. apicalis (Tjeder); 121, A. pruinosa (Tjeder); 122, A. nigrosetosa (Tjeder). Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335160/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 117</figureCitation>
). It also differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[1168,1317,1645,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Afroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequabilis">
<emphasis box="[1168,1317,1645,1671]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">A. aequabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having long antennae that reach beyond the pterostigma (
<figureCitation box="[717,800,1680,1707]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–86" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1747,1772]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,200,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[227,1361,200,1699]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 79–86. Afroptera spp. Forewings of the males. 79, A. acuta sp. nov.; 80, A. alba sp. nov.; 81, A. koranna sp. nov.; 82, A. balli sp. nov.; 83, A. cylindrata sp. nov.; 84, A. brinkmani sp. nov.; 85, A. maraisi sp. nov.; 86, A. folia sp. nov. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335146/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[813,859,1681,1708]" captionStart="FIGURE 106" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1742,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[340,1247,558,1714]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 106. Afroptera maraisi sp. nov., male habitus. Forewing length = 22.8 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3407677/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">106</figureCitation>
); while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Tjeder" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[980,1130,1681,1707]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Afroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aequabilis">
<emphasis box="[980,1130,1681,1707]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">A. aequabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the antennae are short, not reaching the pterostigma.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,1393,2032]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1752,1779]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Description.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[351,396,1753,1779]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Size</emphasis>
(mm). Male: body length 9.7 (9–10.2); forewing 23 (22.4–23.3); hind wing 48.0 (47.6–50.6); antenna 18.9 (16–20.4). 
<typeStatus box="[426,530,1789,1815]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Holotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount box="[538,559,1790,1816]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation box="[575,674,1789,1816]" captionStart="FIGURE 106" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1742,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[340,1247,558,1714]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 106. Afroptera maraisi sp. nov., male habitus. Forewing length = 22.8 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3407677/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
); Body length 8.4; forewing 22.8; hind wing 47.9; antenna 19.7. (N = 3).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="50.[151,1437,1393,2032]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1861,1887]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Head</emphasis>
. Frons, clypeus yellow. Vertex brown with two yellow areas laterally at hind margin and two ill-defined lateral yellow spots on each side near eye margins. Antennae long, reaching pterostigma, scape yellowish brown, pedicel yellow, proximal portion yellowish brown with scattered short setae, dark brown distally with long black setae (
<figureCitation box="[222,321,1969,1996]" captionStart="FIGURE 106" captionStartId="51.[151,250,1742,1767]" captionTargetId="figure@51.[340,1247,558,1714]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 106. Afroptera maraisi sp. nov., male habitus. Forewing length = 22.8 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3407677/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 106</figureCitation>
). Apical segment mostly membranous (
<figureCitation box="[764,848,1969,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 56–66" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1562,1587]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,237,1500]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[227,1361,227,1505]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 56–66.Antennae of Afroptera spp. 56, A. acuta sp. nov.; 57, A. alba sp. nov.; 58, A. koranna sp. nov.; 59, A. folia sp. nov.; 60, A. cylindrata sp. nov.; 61, A. balli sp. nov.; 62, A. maraisi sp. nov.; 63, A. apicalis (Tjeder); 64, A. bitis (Tjeder); 65, A. aequabilis (Tjeder); 66, A. brinkmani sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335142/files/figure.png" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
). Eyes large with diameter approximaly same length as genae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,152,539]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis box="[199,280,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Thorax</emphasis>
. Greyish, pruinose (
<figureCitation box="[511,596,152,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 50–53" captionStartId="37.[151,264,1374,1399]" captionTargetBox="[251,1338,529,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[249,1338,528,1342]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 50–53. Thorax of Afroptera spp. 50, A. cylindrata sp. nov; 51, A. brinkmani sp. nov; 52, A. koranna sp. nov.; 53, A. maraisi sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335138/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
). Pronotum with ill-defined stripes with only midstripe that is traceable as brownish grey shading posteriorly, while the lateral stripes form two lateral brown transverse spots. Pronotal margins with erect long black hairs intermixed with some long, soft white hairs; soft, white hairs situated behind black hairs on fore margin. Distal anterior lateral margins with very long black hairs admixed with white hairs, long, soft white hairs also present on disc. Midstripe on prescutum appears as light brown shading but indistinct on mesoscutellum. Stiff long black hairs present on anterior lateral portions of prescutum admixed with white long hairs. Long sparse black hairs present on disc, with long soft white hairs along lateral margins of prescutum. Mesoscutum with faint brown lateral stripes. Short white hairs on disc, two lateral long tufts of white hairs at each side. Mesoscutellum with scattered short white hairs over whole disc and two groups of long white hair at each side. Metanotum with very long white hairs laterally on hind margin. 
<emphasis box="[680,733,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Legs</emphasis>
yellow, with short setae. Femoral and tibial apices tinged dark brown, fore coxae with black and white setae.
</paragraph>
<caption box="[151,1021,1742,1767]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3407677/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" targetBox="[340,1247,558,1714]" targetPageId="51">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1021,1742,1767]" box="[151,1021,1742,1767]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,301,1742,1767]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">FIGURE 106.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole, 2019" authorityName="Abdalla &amp; Mansell &amp; Sole" authorityYear="2019" box="[307,488,1742,1766]" class="Insecta" family="Nemopteridae" genus="Afroptera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maraisi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[307,488,1742,1766]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Afroptera maraisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[494,575,1743,1767]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[494,575,1743,1767]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, male habitus. Forewing length = 22.8 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1812,2019]" lastBlockId="52.[151,1437,153,611]" lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis box="[199,318,1814,1839]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Forewings</emphasis>
. Appearing elongate, tapering towards apex, weakly emarginated before acute apex (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1423,1812,1839]" captionStart="FIGURES 79–86" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1747,1772]" captionTargetBox="[227,1361,200,1699]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[227,1361,200,1699]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 79–86. Afroptera spp. Forewings of the males. 79, A. acuta sp. nov.; 80, A. alba sp. nov.; 81, A. koranna sp. nov.; 82, A. balli sp. nov.; 83, A. cylindrata sp. nov.; 84, A. brinkmani sp. nov.; 85, A. maraisi sp. nov.; 86, A. folia sp. nov. Scale = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3335146/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 85</figureCitation>
). Pterostigma dark brown, broad at base, long but not reaching C. Costal cells before and beyond pterostigma slightly tinged brown. Venation dark brown. 
<collectingRegion box="[568,632,1885,1911]" country="New Zealand" name="West Coast" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Costa</collectingRegion>
whitish but appearing blackish due to dense black setae. Subcosta and R light brown. Proximal Cx shaded brown. Costal cells increase gradually in size towards pterostigma. 
<typeStatus box="[1332,1436,1921,1947]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Holotype</typeStatus>
with 18 Cx before pterostigma in right wing, 
<quantity box="[653,709,1957,1983]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.334" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" unit="in" value="21.0">21 in</quantity>
left. Ten crossveins between R and M before origin of Rs in right wing, 
<quantity box="[221,277,1993,2019]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
left. Eight radial crossveins before pterostigma in right wing, 
<quantity box="[974,1031,1993,2019]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
left. 
<emphasis box="[1089,1217,1993,2019]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Hind wings</emphasis>
pale creamy white. Proximal portion appears brown. Longitudinal veins pale creamy white, while crossveins appear much darker. Median portion before dark area white, longitudinal veins and crossveins white, dark area dark brown, shorter than white area.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1437,153,611]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[199,305,261,287]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Yellowish brown, tergites with yellowish hind margins. Longitudinal midstripe dark brown. Pleurites pruinose, tergites with dense, long white setae. Venter light reddish yellow, pruinose, with long white hairs but shorter than on tergites. Apex yellow with dense, long black setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="52.[151,1437,153,611]" box="[199,1283,369,395]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis box="[199,303,370,395]" italics="true" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Variation</emphasis>
. Some males have a few black hairs intermingled with the white hairs on the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
